properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 4 at 3:02PM CST until February 6 at 12:00AM CST by NWS Kansas City/Pleasant HIll MO
properties.description:
...Winter Weather Tuesday and Wednesday...

Snow chances will increase across the region by Wednesday
morning. The best potential for accumulating snow will be across
central Missouri into the Ozarks and southeastern Kansas; however,
light snow is possible as far north as the highway 36 corridor in
northern Missouri eastward into north-central and northeast
Missouri.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 1 to 3
inches.

* WHERE...Portions of north central and northeast Missouri.

* WHEN...From 6 PM this evening to midnight CST Wednesday night.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1 in Kansas or visiting
traveler.modot.org for Missouri.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO MIDNIGHT CST WEDNESDAY NIGHT
